assembled and shipped to your door in five or six days. But try to
order a car from the factory that way, and watch out. Buyers who
place such orders face stupefyingly complex forms, then face a wait
long enough to try anyone's patience. Automakers have long been
aware of the problem, but now they are striving to speed things up.
By Keith Bradsher.
