   WAGNER-RING (New York) _ A Critic's Notebook: No ``Ring'' cycle
guarantees customer satisfaction. Wagner's four-evening, weeklong
operatic monster, known officially as ``Der Ring des Niebelungen,''
has too many spiritual and physical moving parts to inspire
consensus. Barter and negotiation occupy the minds and hearts of
every audience member: what must I surrender to gain what I most
value? The trades are not easily made. By Bernard Holland.
