<SLUG> BC-BBA-ANGELS-NOTEBOOK-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
DISARCINA PLACED ON 15-DAY DISABLED LIST
</HEADLINE>
 
Eds: Updates with DiSarcina going on DL (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BILLY WITZ  
 c.2000 Long Beach Press-Telegram  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ANAHEIM, Calif. _ Shortstop Gary DiSarcina was placed on the
15-day disabled list after Monday night's game with a sore right
shoulder. Tests will be done today to determine the severity of the
injury.
</P>
<P>
   DiSarcina played his first game in six days Monday but came out
after the fifth inning when, for the second time in the game, he
bounced a throw to first base.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're all concerned,'' said Angels manager Mike Scioscia, who
announced the team will recall middle infielder Trent Durrington
from Triple-A Edmonton. ``Gary's a gamer. I can't overstate what he
means to this team, not only to the infield but the whole makeup of
this team.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's lingering with him. It's been like hit or miss. He had
three great workouts in Seattle and in the game it went south.''
</P>
<P>
   The Angels record is roughly the same with DiSarcina in the
lineup (7-5) as it is without him (10-11), but they clearly aren't
the same team. He's their most reliable infielder and he entered
Monday's game batting .361.
</P>
<P>
   DiSarcina doubled to drive in two runs in his first at-bat
Monday and his perfectly placed hit-and-run single in the fourth
led to another run.
</P>
<P>
   INJURIES ELSEWHERE: Tim Belcher's recovery from offseason elbow
surgery took another turn for the worse Monday when an MRI revealed
the right-handed pitcher has inflammation in his right elbow.
</P>
<P>
   The Angels were hopeful that Belcher, who underwent elbow
surgery in November, would be ready to join the team at the
beginning of this month. But he experienced soreness after his last
minor-league rehabilitation start April 25 and has twice been
scratched from scheduled rehab appearances.
</P>
<P>
   Team officials, in making the announcement Monday night, said
the inflammation is not related to the surgery and that Belcher
won't throw again until it subsides.
</P>
<P>
   Jason Dickson, another pitcher on the mend, threw in the bullpen
before Monday night's game. He is due to come off the 15-day
disabled list Saturday after straining a right hip flexor muscle.
</P>
<P>
   Kent Mercker, who threw five scoreless innings Saturday against
Seattle, will again take Dickson's place in the rotation and pitch
Thursday against Texas. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-05-09-00 0317EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
