   TEXAS AT LARGE-CHAPMAN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ The Texas Historical Commission says that Texas _ not
surprisingly, with 254 counties _ has more historic courthouses
than any other state. ``Today, more than 225 courthouses still
stand that are at least 50 years old,'' the commission says.
``About 80 were built before the turn of the century. Most of these
structures have deteriorated significantly due to either
abandonment, inadequate maintenance, insensitive modifications or a
combination of those problems.'' This month, the commission took a
major step in improving those conditions by awarding 19 grants to
counties for courthouse improvements. By ART CHAPMAN. Story has
moved in ``a'' general news category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
