<SLUG> BC-ART-WEBSITES-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CLICKING ON CULTURE
</HEADLINE>
 
(EDS: Accompanies INTERNET-ART) (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   There are a dizzying number of Internet sites catering to all
manner of art lovers _ too many for even the most dedicated
aficionado to check out. Below are a handful of top sites for
Internet-art newcomers seeking to view, appreciate, research and
buy art:
</P>
<P>
   www.circline.com _ A premier site specializing in
dealer-provided art, antiques, accessories and other decorative
arts.
</P>
<P>
   www.artcellarexchange.com _ Provides a raft of appraisal and
other information to help users make ``intelligent acquisitions''
of fine art. Also stocks interesting originals.
</P>
<P>
   www.artnet.com _ Makes available pricier items, from $200 to
$5,000, in addition to a database of a decade's worth of key
auction statistics. Specializes in theme art shows such as
currently running ``Classics of the 20th Century.''
</P>
<P>
   www.artstar.com _ Has a grab bag of things artistic, including
numerous gallery listings, many thousands of images, and even
biographies of various artists. Can provide some very expensive
items but mostly sells posters and reproductions for less than $50.
</P>
<P>
   www.sothebys.amazon.com _ Provides access to art, furniture,
jewelry, books and silver in roughly the $100 to $10,000 range.
</P>
<P>
   www.sothebys.com _ Many of the sothebys.amazon items are
available here, but only in a more stratospheric price range (up to
$100,000).
</P>
<P>
   www.nextmonet.com _ Specializing in originals from upand-coming
artists. The price range tends to be between $100 and $1,200.
</P>
<P>
   www.visualize.com _ Commands a wide market in both the originals
and limited-editions online market, again culled from collections
of cutting-edge artists. The price range is from $90 to $1,000.
</P>
<P>
   www.guild.com _ Discerning market for crafts and decorative arts
is the twin areas of this largely direct-sale site. Its average
range is $100 to $500.
</P>
<P>
   www.artmuseum.net _ Tour various blockbuster museum shows
constructed from real exhibits at, among others, the San Francisco
Modern Museum of Art or the Whitney Museum of American Art.
</P>
<P>
   www.frameyourart.com _ Just what it says, one of the Net's more
popular customized framing sites.
</P>
<P>
   _ Andrew Marton
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
