<P>
   NIGERIA-ABACHA (Geneva, Switzerland) _ Authorities pursuing what
Nigeria says is billions of dollars looted from the country during
the rule of the late strongman Sani Abacha say they have found $630
million in Luxembourg bank accounts connected with his sons. By
Elizabeth Olson.
</P>
<P>
   TURKEY-ARMENIANS (Elazig, Turkey) _ Groves of mulberry trees at
lakeside resorts are about all that remain from the days when this
region was a center of Armenian life. Here in eastern Turkey, the
passage of several generations has not been enough to wipe the
killings of 1915 from memory. To most Turks the events of 1915 seem
distant, but in the Armenian consciousness they are a vivid and
constant presence. Awareness of what is simply called ``the
genocide'' is acute in Armenian communities around the world. By
Stephen Kinzer.
</P>
<P>
   (MOVED)
</P>
<P>
   PALESTINIAN-ANTHEM (Bethlehem, West Bank) _ With scores of
pinstriped businessmen milling about the hotel ballroom, it looked
like any other shareholders meeting. But when the meeting was
called to order, the first piece of business was a song. A sheet of
lyrics in Arabic was distributed for the few who did not already
know the words. Everyone rose, and with swelling emotion sang every
verse of ``My Homeland,'' the unofficial Palestinian national
anthem. By William A. Orme Jr.
</P>
<P>
   (MOVED)
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL GENERAL
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in ``a'' news file.)
