<P>
   MIAMI-POLITICS (Miami) _ Mayor of Miami appoints a new city
manager and lots of people are talking about the fact that all top
jobs are now held by cuban americans. No one might have noticed
that if it all had not happened in the wake of the Elian Gonzalez
case. Now, however, ethnic sensitivities are heightened here. By
Rick Bragg.
</P>
<P>
   TENN-FOSTER-CASE (Knoxville, Tenn.) _ Marcia Lowry, the lawyer
whose lawsuit brought major changes to New York's foster care
program, is suing to bring similar changes in Tennessee. Of the
9,000 children in the state's system, hundreds have been in as many
as a dozen homes, some with squalid conditions. The suit, which is
being filed Tuesday, also accuses the states of treating black
children worse than white children. By Emily Yellin.
</P>
