<P>
   AT&AMP;T-MARKETPLACE (Undated) _ Investors who missed out on the
biggest-ever U.S. initial stock offering last month need not worry
or hurry. Shares of AT&AMP;T Wireless Group are back down at their
offering price and, judging by Tuesday's trading pattern, may not
be heading back up again soon. By Patrick McGeehan with Seth
Schiesel.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 8:30 p.m. ET.)
</P>
<P>
   (Center display)
</P>
<P>
   CIO-MANAGEMENT (Undated) _ In corporate America, an increasing
number of chief information officers _ the folks in charge of the
computers _ are amassing greater power as top bosses and company
boards realize how crucial technical expertise is in staying ahead
of the competition. A recent survey found that companies are
increasingly looking to a new generation of chief information
officers to be business strategists, and that these ``new'' CIOs
spend at least half their time outside the information-technology
department on efforts like developing and incubating new prospects
for electronic commerce. By Sana Siwolop.
</P>
