   McCAIN-2004 (Washington) _ Republican John McCain positions
himself for a comeback presidential bid in 2004 with his belated
endorsement of this year's presumptive GOP nominee, George W. Bush.
The Republican insurgent embraces the Texas governor with just
enough calculated enthusiasm to avoid being blamed if Bush loses in
November. News analysis. By STEWART M. POWELL. (Already filed.)
WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
