<P>
   AIRLINE-SURVEY (Washington) _ Continental Airlines ranks highest
among major domestic carriers in customer satisfaction for both
short and long flights, according to a new study of consumer
attitudes. TWA finishes a close second and Southwest a distant
third in the survey of more than 6,000 frequent flyers. By AUSTIN
ZALKIN. (Already filed.)
