   MISSILE-DEFENSE (Washington) _ Lt. Gen. Ronald Kadish, the Air
Force official responsible for managing a controversial project to
defend the country against missile attacks, says he is confident
that next month's crucial test flight of the system will succeed,
setting the stage for President Clinton to approve the missile
system. By ERIC ROSENBERG. (Already filed.) MILLION-MOM-MARCH
