other cities this Sunday that will press for tougher gun laws, Sen.
Dianne Feinstein, D-Calif., introduces legislation that would
require buyers of handguns and some semi-automatic weapons to be
licensed. By JUDY HOLLAND. (Already filed.) CHINA-TRADE
(Washington) _ Former Presidents Carter and Ford and a who's who
from Republican and Democratic administrations join President
Clinton in pressing Congress to grant permanent normal trade
relations to China. By BENNETT ROTH.
</P>
<P>
   NINA-COAST (Washington) _ La Nina, the Pacific Ocean cold-water
mass blamed for last summer's droughts and hurricanes, is on its
last legs, NASA reports. For the West Coast, this means winters
less cold and less wet. But NASA scientists are watching a
reappearance of warmer-than-normal water off the coast of South
America. In 1997, the warm El Nino water generated devastating
storms on the U.S. West Coast. By DAN FREEDMAN. (Already filed.)
</P>
