<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRON </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (Eds: This story also moved in the ``a'' national news file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.2000 San Francisco Chronicle  
 
 
 CLINTON LIES DOWN WITH DOG 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Returning to the White House after the funeral for  &UR; Cardinal &LR; 
 &UR; John O'Connor &LR;  on Monday, May 8, in New York,  &UR; Bill Clinton &LR;  was
greeted by his dog,  &UR; Buddy &LR; , to whom he immediately tossed a tennis
ball.
</P>
<P>
   ``He sleeps with me when Hillary's not here,'' said the
president. ``He's my true friend. We have a great time.'' Buddy is
said to be working on a signature handbag collection.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; RATINGS FOR EVERYTHING EVERYWHERE &LR;
</P>
<P>
   American Heritage magazine's annual Overrated and Underrated
List _ that magazine's answer to People's 50 Most Beautiful _ is
out, with the lead entry written by San Francisco journalist
 &UR; Richard Reinhardt &LR; . His view:  &UR; Amelia Earhart &LR; , ``recruited as
deliberately as Elizabeth Doolittle was plucked from the streets of
London by Professor Higgins,'' is the most overrated aviatrix; and
 &UR; Harriet Quimby &LR; , the first American woman to become a licensed
pilot, the most underrated.
</P>
<P>
   The Soviet Union was the most overrated enemy, writes  &UR; T.A. &LR; 
 &UR; Heppenheimer &LR; , and Canada _ which U.S. forces tried twice,
unsuccessfully, to annex _ the most underrated.  &UR; Liz Smith &LR;  writes
that the most overrated love affair was between the  &UR; Duke &LR;  and
 &UR; Duchess of Windsor &LR;  (``less passion and romance than obsession and
misadventure''); the most underrated was between  &UR; Harry S. &LR;  and
 &UR; Bess Truman &LR;  (his ``heart remained on fire for the young girl he
had married'').
</P>
<P>
   Most overrated '60s counterculture heroes are  &UR; Abbie Hoffman &LR; 
and  &UR; Jerry Rubin &LR; , writes  &UR; David Obst &LR; . Most underrated is local
favorite  &UR; Stewart Brand &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   P.S. Elsewhere in the world of awards,  &UR; John Carter &LR;  of San
Rafael writes to Personals proposing the Faked Outrage Hall of
Fame. Carter's first nominees were  &UR; Newt Gingrich &LR; ,  &UR; Clarence &LR; 
 &UR; Thomas &LR;  and  &UR; Orrin Hatch &LR; , but he says they've since taken a
backseat to the Miami relatives of  &UR; Elian Gonzalez &LR; . Suggestions,
anyone?
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; BEING THE BEST &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; THAT THEY CAN BE &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Hugh Grant &LR;  told TV Guide Online that he's had three
celebrity obsessions in his life:  &UR; Queen &LR;   &UR; Elizabeth &LR; ,  &UR; Woody
Allen &LR;  and Russian gymnast  &UR; Olga Korbut &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL; 
 &LR; _  &UR; Liza Minnelli &LR;  said on ``Sunday Morning'' this week that she's
thinking about working with underprivileged children in Peru.
``It's just the possibilities,'' she said, ``and it's the
possibilities that I love, you know.'' Meanwhile,  &UR; Prince Andrew &LR; ,
equally committed to possibilities, told Tatler magazine that he
doesn't rule out remarriage to the  &UR; Duchess of York &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL; 
 &LR; _ Self magazine shares a series of brain exercises to ``keep you
sharp for decades,'' including reading a book in the mirror. ``If
that makes you nauseated (it might), wear your watch upside down.''
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ Little, Brown and Co. has canceled plans to publish a book
about  &UR; John F. Kennedy Jr. &LR;  by the former editor in chief of George
magazine because the publisher learned that author  &UR; Rich &LR; 
 &UR; Blow &LR;  had signed a confidentiality agreement with the magazine.
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL; 
 &LR; _  &UR; Doris Kearns Goodwin &LR;  jumped out of a fake birthday cake on
Sunday, May 7, at  &UR; Tim Russert &LR; 's 50th birthday party and
lip-synched to  &UR; Marilyn Monroe &LR;  singing ``Happy Birthday'' to &UR; JFK &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``Fishnets are back, but only for entertaining chez vous. Wear &LR; 
 &UR; dark brown fishnets with an oversized off-white Aran sweater and &LR; 
 &UR; nothing else. ... A word of caution: Do not wear fishnets &LR; 
 &UR; unless your legs are really fat or really thin. Ordinary legs &LR; 
 &UR; look dreadful in them.'' &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ &UR; Simon Doonan &LR;  in the New York Observer.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; (For use by New York Times News Service Clients) &QL;  &LR;
</P>
