<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Are you the multimillionaire?
 &HT;    (Eds: Fixes winning numbers, recasts lede.)
 &HT;    By Gita Smith
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ 1, 2, 12, 33, 37. Money ball: 4.
</P>
<P>
   Those were the numbers drawn Tuesday night in Atlanta in the
record-jackpot Big Game lottery drawing. Lottery officials in seven
participating Big Game states worked into the wee hours making
their lists and checking them twice to see whether somebody won the
$350 million jackpot that has been growing since March 7.
</P>
<P>
   Is he or she out there right now, getting a new, unlisted phone
number, or will the jackpot grow, yet again? The answer was not
expected until about 5 a.m. Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   A sole winner would receive either $8.9 million a year for 26
years or a one-time payment of $114 million after taxes. Those
numbers are based on Georgia state taxes, and would change slightly
if the winner bought the ticket in another state.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
