</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; NETWORTH (COLUMN) _  &LR; It was a sober crowd at the Chase H&AMP;Q
Technology Conference luncheon Tuesday, and not just because there
was no wine on the menu.  &UR; COLUMN BY KATHLEEN PENDER &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; VC_  &LR; Venture capital investors poured more than $1 billion a week
into promising U.S. startups in the first quarter, and Bay Area
companies once again received a disproportionate share of the
bounty.  &UR; WITH SIDEBAR. BY PETER SINTON &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; GROW (GROW A BUSINESS COLUMN) _  &LR; Home remodeler Judith Thompson's
flourishing business illustrates how entrepreneurs can sometimes
avoid the mass market and succeed in the process.
 &UR; COLUMN BY PETER SINTON &LR;
</P>
